Poultry Vaccines and Drugs Market Report
Market Overview
The global poultry vaccines and drugs market is valued at approximately $12.5 billion in 2025, with a projected compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of 6.8% from 2023 to 2030. This growth is driven by increasing poultry production, growing prevalence of avian diseases, and the need for efficient vaccines and drugs to ensure food safety and productivity.

The market includes a wide array of products such as live, inactivated, and recombinant vaccines alongside antibiotics and antiviral drugs. Technological advancements, improved disease diagnostics, and a rising demand for animal protein contribute significantly to the market expansion.

